# ShelfEdit UI Style — soft precision

Use this visual language for future ShelfEdit web, desktop, extension, and tool
interfaces. The target feel is soft precision: calm, rounded, compact,
engineered, and trustworthy.

## Core Direction

- Design a custom interface for each app. Do not accept the default SwiftUI,
  AppKit, Qt, browser, or OS-native control look as the final UI.
- For Swift/macOS apps, Apple-native video and media APIs are still preferred for
  performance, but the editor chrome, timeline, inspector, transport, panels,
  buttons, and controls should be custom-styled/drawn to match this design
  system.
- Do not use WebView or HTML to transport decoded video frames. Web/native/custom
  UI choices must not break the zero-copy or near-zero-copy media path.
- Use Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif everywhere.
- Default canvas/background is dark grey, around `#202020` to `#2b2b2b`.
  Individual top-level boxes/cards are white unless the screen explicitly needs
  a black/dark media surface.
- Avoid parent and child boxes with the same fill color. If a parent box is
  white, child boxes must use off-white, light grey, or a semantic light color;
  if a parent uses a semantic light color, children should use white or a
  visibly different semantic tint.
- No thin borders anywhere. Use soft shadows, inset shadows, fills, and spacing
  instead of 1px outline borders.
- Every component that floats above another surface needs a shadow.
- Spacing between sibling boxes should be compact: about 1.5x tighter than the
  previous loose dashboard spacing. Prefer 8-16px gaps, not 24-32px gaps.
- Sub-boxes should include a middle/inner strip or visual separator when useful
  for scanning. The strip should be soft and adjustable, not a hard border.
- Only secondary-or-deeper boxes may own a left color rim/accent stripe. The rim
  is optional. Bigger/primary boxes may have no rim.
- Avoid similar color stacks such as grey-white-blue-white nested together. Each
  colored surface must have clear contrast against its parent.

## Exact Soft Precision Tokens

Use these values as the source of truth. The style is compact, rounded,
engineered, and calm. It avoids sharpness, loud decoration, and hard borders,
but it should still feel functional and trustworthy.

### Corners

- Small controls: `8-10px` radius.
- Normal buttons / inputs: `10-12px`.
- Cards / panels: `12-16px`.
- Large modal panels: `16-20px`.
- Pills / chips / nav tabs: `999px`.
- Avoid `0-4px` unless the UI is intentionally technical, terminal-like, or
  table-heavy.
- Avoid `24px+` for ordinary dashboards; it can feel toy-like.
- Default tokens:
  - `--radius-control: 10px`
  - `--radius-card: 14px`
  - `--radius-panel: 16px`
  - `--radius-pill: 999px`

### Shadows

- Use shadows for soft separation instead of hard borders.
- Tiny elevation: `0 2px 6px rgba(15,23,42,0.06)`.
- Normal card: `0 8px 24px rgba(15,23,42,0.08)`.
- Hover card: `0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.12)`.
- Floating panel/modal: `0 16px 40px rgba(15,23,42,0.16-0.24)`.
- Comfortable modal: `0 18px 44px rgba(15,23,42,0.22)`.
- Avoid dark shadows above `0.30` opacity unless it is a modal overlay.
- Avoid sharp, short shadows like `0 1px 1px black`.

### Borders

- Prefer invisible or very soft borders.
- Normal border opacity: `0.12-0.25`.
- Input inset border: `rgba(..., 0.35-0.50)`.
- Strong active border: `0.35-0.55`.
- Border width: almost always `1px`.
- For ShelfEdit desktop/editor chrome, avoid visible thin borders; use fills,
  shadows, spacing, and inset input shadows instead.
- Comfortable input inset:
  `box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(148,163,184,0.45)`.

### Buttons

- Buttons are rounded rectangles, compact, and confident.
- Height: `30-40px`.
- Compact toolbar button height: `28-32px`.
- Main button height: `36-44px`.
- Horizontal padding: `12-18px`.
- Vertical padding: `7-10px`.
- Radius: `10-12px`.
- Font size: `12-14px`.
- Font weight: `650-750`, usually `700`.
- Hover lift: `translateY(-1px)` or none.
- Hover brightness shift: `0.94-1.06`.
- Transition: `120-180ms ease`.
- Tiny toolbar icon buttons: `36px` by `36px`, `10px` radius.
- Navigation/filter pills: min-height `28px`, padding `5px 12px`, `999px`
  radius, `12px` text, `700` weight.

### Inputs

- Inputs should feel embedded, not heavily boxed.
- Height: `36-44px`.
- Padding: `9-12px`.
- Radius: `10-12px`.
- Font size: `13-14px`.
- Focus ring: `2-3px` outer glow at `0.14-0.22` opacity.
- Textarea minimum height: `96-300px`, depending on use.
- Focus shadow:
  `inset 0 0 0 1px currentColor, 0 0 0 3px rgba(30,58,138,0.18)`.

### Cards And Panels

- Cards are the main object language.
- Small card width: `280-360px`.
- Medium card width: `420-640px`.
- Large tool panel: `720-1040px`.
- Card padding: `14-20px`.
- Large panel padding: `20-32px`.
- Card radius: `14-16px`.
- Internal gap: `10-16px`.
- Card hover lift: `1-3px`.
- Avoid nested cards unless the inner card is a real repeated item.

### Spacing

- Use a compact but breathable spacing scale:
  - `--space-1: 4px`
  - `--space-2: 8px`
  - `--space-3: 12px`
  - `--space-4: 16px`
  - `--space-5: 20px`
  - `--space-6: 24px`
  - `--space-8: 32px`
  - `--space-10: 40px`
- Gap between icon and text: `6-10px`.
- Gap between form fields: `10-14px`.
- Gap between card sections: `14-24px`.
- Page/content padding: `16-32px`.
- Dense panel padding: `12-16px`.
- Marketing/hero padding: `32-64px`.

### Typography

- Use `Arial, Helvetica, system-ui, sans-serif`.
- Tiny metadata: `10-11px`.
- Secondary metadata: `11-12px`.
- Body UI text: `12-14px`.
- Normal body paragraph: `14-16px`.
- Card heading: `16-21px`.
- Panel heading: `20-28px`.
- Hero heading: `36-56px`.
- Body weight: `400-500`.
- Metadata labels: `600-700`.
- Buttons: `700`.
- Headings: `700-800`.
- Dense UI line-height: `1.2-1.35`.
- Body UI line-height: `1.4-1.5`.
- Reading line-height: `1.55-1.7`.
- Avoid negative letter spacing. Tiny uppercase labels may use `0.03em`.

### Chips / Tags

- Chips are pill-like and compact.
- Height: `22-30px`.
- Padding: `3-8px` or `5-10px`.
- Radius: `999px`.
- Font size: `10-12px`.
- Weight: `700`.
- Uppercase category tags are acceptable.
- Gap between chips: `6px`.

### Modals / Popups

- Popups should feel local and soft.
- Modal radius: `16-20px`.
- Popup radius: `12-14px`.
- Popup padding: `10-16px`.
- Modal padding: `20-28px`.
- Overlay tint: `rgba(15,23,42,0.08-0.24)`.
- Backdrop blur: `1-8px`.
- Popup shadow: `0 14px 34px rgba(15,23,42,0.22-0.28)`.
- Entry motion: `translateY(6-10px) scale(0.96-0.98)` to normal.
- Duration: `160-220ms`.

### Motion

- Motion should be gentle and functional.
- Micro transitions: `120-160ms`.
- Popup transitions: `180-220ms`.
- Page/card focus transitions: `240-420ms`.
- Hover lift: `1-3px`.
- Hover scale: `1.02-1.06`.
- Icon-only playful hover max: `1.08-1.12`.
- Avoid springy/bouncy animation unless the product is playful.

### Layout Density

- Compact, not sparse.
- Sidebar width: `280-320px`.
- Toolbar height: `48-56px`.
- Panel max width for reading: `640-760px`.
- Tool card width: `720-1040px`.
- Form row height: `40-48px`.
- Data row height: `36-52px`.
- Use `12px` or `16px` as the default internal card spacing. Use `24px` only
  for larger separations.

### Plain JS/CSS Reconstruction Reference

When another implementation needs to recreate the scene, start from this exact
token object and apply it before product-specific colors:

```js
const softPrecision = {
  radius: {
    control: 10,
    card: 14,
    panel: 16,
    modal: 18,
    pill: 999,
  },
  shadow: {
    tiny: "0 2px 6px rgba(15,23,42,0.06)",
    card: "0 8px 24px rgba(15,23,42,0.08)",
    hover: "0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.12)",
    popup: "0 14px 34px rgba(15,23,42,0.26)",
    modal: "0 18px 44px rgba(15,23,42,0.22)",
  },
  spacing: {
    xs: 4,
    sm: 8,
    md: 12,
    lg: 16,
    xl: 24,
    xxl: 32,
  },
  typography: {
    family: "Arial, Helvetica, system-ui, sans-serif",
    tiny: 10,
    meta: 11,
    ui: 13,
    body: 14,
    cardHeading: 16,
    panelHeading: 24,
    weightBody: 500,
    weightMeta: 700,
    weightButton: 700,
    weightHeading: 800,
  },
  controls: {
    toolbarHeight: 52,
    compactButtonHeight: 32,
    buttonHeight: 36,
    mainButtonHeight: 40,
    inputHeight: 40,
    chipHeight: 24,
    buttonPaddingX: 14,
    inputPaddingX: 12,
  },
  motion: {
    microMs: 140,
    popupMs: 200,
    focusMs: 320,
    hoverLiftPx: -1,
    cardLiftPx: -2,
  },
};
```

## Website UI

- Page background: gradient from `#f8fafc` into pale indigo `#eef2ff`, plus a
  soft dot grid using `#94a3b8` at 35% opacity.
- Top bar: fixed 52px height, translucent white `rgba(255,255,255,0.88)`,
  `backdrop-filter: blur(10px)`, and soft shadow separation. It should feel
  like frosted glass without a hard border.
- Cards: white `#ffffff`, `border-radius: 16px`, shadow
  `0 12px 34px rgba(15,23,42,0.08)`.
- Hover cards: lift upward 2px and use shadow
  `0 8px 18px rgba(15,23,42,0.1)`.
- Inner cards/tiles: `border-radius: 12px`.

## Buttons And Controls

- Primary buttons: navy `#1e3a8a`, white text, `border-radius: 10px`, no border,
  bold text. Website buttons use `padding: 8px 14px`, `font-size: 12px`,
  `font-weight: 700`. Hover: `filter: brightness(0.96)`.
- Secondary buttons: light slate `#e2e8f0`, text `#0f172a`, same rounded shape.
- Account button: pill shape, `border-radius: 999px`, gradient
  `linear-gradient(160deg, #2f6fd0, #1c5ca8)`, white text, small shadow
  `0 1px 2px rgba(3,16,31,0.25)`.
- Nav buttons: pill links, `border-radius: 999px`, `font-size: 13px`,
  `font-weight: 600`, muted text `#64748b`.
- Active nav: text `#1e3a8a`, background `rgba(28,92,168,0.10)`, shadow or
  color fill for emphasis.
- Language select: compact rounded rectangle, background `#e2e8f0`, no border,
  `border-radius: 10px`, `font-size: 12px`, bold.

## Typography And Color

- Main text: `#1f2937`.
- Headings: `#0f172a`.
- Body/help text: `#475569` or `#64748b`.
- Muted text: `#94a3b8`.
- Heading scale: brand 18px / 700; normal card headings 16px; hero headline
  20px; large download title 40px / 800; global stats heading 26px.
- Tag pills: uppercase, `font-size: 10px`, `font-weight: 700`,
  `letter-spacing: 0.04em`, `border-radius: 999px`, `padding: 3px 8px`.

## Fixed Semantic Colors

Use these precise light/heavy pairs. Colored backgrounds use the heavier variant
when contrast matters.

- Assets:
  - light: `#e0f2fe`
  - heavy: `#0284c7`
- Video:
  - light: `#dbeafe`
  - heavy: `#1d4ed8`
- Audio:
  - light: `#fce7f3`
  - heavy: `#be185d`
- Text:
  - light: `#ecfeff`
  - heavy: `#0891b2`
- Export:
  - light: `#fef3c7`
  - heavy: `#b45309`
- AI:
  - default: `#ffffff`
  - fallback when white conflicts with the background: use export gold
    `#fef3c7` / `#b45309`
- Generic buttons:
  - light: `#f1f5f9`
  - heavy: `#64748b`
- Danger:
  - light: `#fee2e2`
  - heavy: `#b91c1c`
- Neutral surfaces:
  - canvas dark grey: `#202020`
  - secondary canvas dark grey: `#2b2b2b`
  - child off-white: `#f8fafc`
  - box white: `#ffffff`
  - dark media surface: `#111827`

If a feature is not covered by this map, do not invent a color silently. Ask the
user or use neutral/generic grey until a precise color is assigned.

## Legacy Semantic Tag Colors

- Home/platform: background `#eef2ff`, text `#1e3a8a`.
- Feature/free/custom: background `#fffbeb`, text `#854d0e`.
- Account/snooze: background `#fdf2f8`, text `#9d174d`.
- Download/filter/cyan: background `#ecfeff`, text `#155e75`.
- Docs/slate: background `#e2e8f0`, text `#475569`.
- Danger: background `#fee2e2`, text `#991b1b`.

## Inputs And Feedback

- Inputs: white background, no visible border, inset border via
  `box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(148,163,184,0.45)`, `border-radius: 10px`.
- Input focus: `0 0 0 3px rgba(30,58,138,0.18)` plus navy inset outline.
- Focus arrows: perfect circles, 42px by 42px, white
  `rgba(255,255,255,0.96)`, navy arrow `#1c5ca8`, shadow
  `0 4px 14px rgba(3,16,31,0.22)`.
  Hover scales to 1.12.
- Popup feedback overlay: local to each card. Soft dim `rgba(15,23,42,0.05)`,
  message card white, `border-radius: 12px`, shadow
  `0 14px 34px rgba(15,23,42,0.26)`, animated from
  `translateY(8px) scale(0.97)` to normal.

## Extension / App UI

- Same font: Arial, sans-serif.
- Browser extension popups may keep the light vertical gradient `#f8fafc` to
  `#eef2ff`.
- ShelfEdit desktop/editor app backgrounds use the dark grey canvas
  `#202020` / `#2b2b2b`; top-level boxes float above it in white.
- Main panels: translucent white `rgba(255,255,255,0.92)`, `border-radius: 16px`,
  shadow `0 12px 34px rgba(15,23,42,0.08)`.
- App buttons are smaller: primary navy `#1e3a8a`, white text,
  `border-radius: 10px`, `font-size: 10px`, `font-weight: 700`,
  `padding: 5px 8px`.
- Group cards: pale navy-white mix, `border-radius: 12px`, shadow
  `0 4px 14px rgba(15,23,42,0.06)`.
- Active group: `#eef2ff` with shadow `0 8px 18px rgba(30,58,138,0.16)`.
- Section cards: `border-radius: 12px`, soft background tint, no border, left
  vertical accent stripe 4px wide with rounded right edge. This is a major style
  signature.

## Summary Signature

Smooth rounded vertices, soft glass/chrome, navy primary actions, slate text,
pastel semantic panels, compact Arial typography, no hard borders, shadows
instead of outlines, and pill controls for nav/tags/segmented actions.
